e Monáe's music videos, and her own artistic practice, cárdenas shows how algorithmic analysis provides new modes of understanding the complex processes of identity and oppression and the intersection of gender, sexuality, and race.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDigital media. 0aGender identity in art. 0aMinority artists. 0aMinority authors. 0aTransgender artists. 0aTransgender people's writings. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Transgender Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074331940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478022275?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022275423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022275/original  a978-3-11-074331-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles